just_use study.py

# label: TOOL (board-lab)
# role: read BOARD_LAB sessions for analysis

Reads `lynrummy_puzzle_seeds` + `lynrummy_elm_actions` and
prints every human+agent attempt at a named puzzle. One
primitive per line with the spatial facts that matter:
cards involved, pre-move landing loc, merge side, drag
endpoint coords, sample count.

A short `--- divergences ---` block at the bottom of each
puzzle flags primitive-count mismatches, kind-sequence
mismatches, and first-move landing-loc differences. Points
the analyst at where to look without claiming judgment.

## Usage

    python3 games/lynrummy/python/study.py
        # puzzle index: table of puzzle_names with session counts
    python3 games/lynrummy/python/study.py tight_right_edge
        # every attempt at one puzzle, side by side
    python3 games/lynrummy/python/study.py --all
        # dump every puzzle's sessions

## First-use finding

Surfaced the `find_open_loc → (7, 7)` weakness on 2026-04-23:
agent consistently lands pre-moves at the top-left corner,
human lands at `y ≈ 94-116`. See
`claude-steve/board_lab_analysis.md` for the writeup and
candidate fix.

## Pointers

- DB source: `~/AngryGopher/prod/gopher.db` (override with
  `--db PATH`).
- Capture side: `agent_board_lab.py` writes agent rows;
  BOARD_LAB's Elm Lab writes human rows.
